CONTRACTORS, PACIFIC NAVAL AIR BASES, et al., Appellants, v. OLIVER J. OLSON & CO., Appellee. No. 10842. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Aug. 2, 1944. Frank J. Hennessy, U. S. Atty., and Esther B. Phillips, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of San Francisco, Cal., for appellants. Herman Phleger and J. S. Moore, Jr., both of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before DENMAN, MATHEWS, and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of the stipulation of counsel for respective parties, and good cause therefor appearing, it is ordered that the appeal in above cause be dismissed, without costs, that a decree be filed and entered accordingly and that the mandate of this Court in this cause issue forthwith.
